  "prompt": "What is the difference (if any) between transgender and transexual?",
  "response": "The terms \"transgender\" and \"transsexual\" have some nuanced differences:\n\nTransgender:\n- Broader term\n- Refers to people whose gender identity differs from their sex assigned at birth\n- Includes people who may or may not choose to medically transition\n- Encompasses a wide range of gender identities and expressions\n\nTranssexual:\n- Narrower, more specific term\n- Typically refers to individuals who have undergone or plan to undergo medical transition (hormones, surgery)\n- Often implies a stronger emphasis on physical/medical transformation\n- Some consider this term somewhat outdated\n\nToday, \"transgender\" is more commonly used and generally considered more respectful. Many people prefer to be identified simply as transgender, regardless of their medical transition status.\n\nThe most important thing is to respect how individuals choose to identify themselves and use the terms they prefer.",
